O-KQ

Keeping the Common common

Common land In 1965 An act of Parliament Commons Registration Act hoped to register all common land. It then defined what was allowed on Common Land 1 1/2 million acres of common land exists in England and Wales. Since 1965

Land Certificate at Penn Road Beaconsfield

The Certificate refers to the conveyance of land between James Scott McBride & Olga Elaine McBride (Vendors) and Mark Scott Constructions Limited (purchaser) and refers to an original agreement dated 20 October 1906 between The Right Honourable Richard George Penn Earl Howe (Vendor) and The Honourable Francis Richard Henry Penn Curzon-Howe & Henry Herbert Robinson ...

P-TFL

Large black and white photograph of Dick Smith

On reverse details of appointment to Town Cryer in 1969 when 22 and he won the National Championships at Hastings in 1969-70. His bell cast in1797records the names and dates of town criers since 1862

G-BG/R/014

Large bound collection of annual books 1933-1936 Parish Magazine

See individual annual entries for details. A bound version of the magazine on local information and events. In July on page 48 there is obituary of Viscount Burnham 20th July 1933. In September on page 54 there is a photograph of Viscount Burnham 1862-1933.

B-SMAS/B/042

Large hardback book St Mary & All Saints, Beaconsfield, Coal Club

Lists of names of locals and the regular weekly payments throughout the years 1925-1935 on account for coal

B-SMAS/X/042

Large landscape book - The Turnpike Age

History of roads, their repairs by locals who were obliged by Parliament to turn out 4 days a year to help maintain roads and later the passing of an act in 1621 insisting on tolls to repair roads from the north to London which preceded the eventual introduction of the Turnpike Act of ...

P-HC/B/006

Large volume of magazines 1929 - 1932 Parish Magazine

Large bound book including 1929 not available as individual annual collection. A bound version of the magazine on local information and events. In January on page 6 there is an article by Thomas Lane, “Reminiscences of Beaconsfield during the past fifty years”, referring to the use of trade tokens in the town. In ...

Leaflet "Surprise yourself .join the Royal British Legion Women's section"

Details about the Royal British Legion women’s section including what they do -care and support for the community , membership and activities
